      <div id="intro" class="intro"> <img src="images/tna-centenary-map-falklands.png" title="The Falkland islands" alt="Small outline image of the Falkland islands" class="float-right" />
        <p>The Falkland Islands are a small group of islands in the South Atlantic Ocean, approximately 300 miles east of the Argentinian coast. The Islands are a British protectorate. Britain took possession of the Falkland Islands and Dependencies in 1833 and installed a lieutenant-governor (later governor) in 1842.</p>
        <p>The Falklands were an important military base for the British during the First World War and later the Second World War. The key event for the Falklands during the First World War occurred in the last few months of 1914.</p>
        <div class="clear5px"></div>
